The ſecond Reaſon is, becauſe the Scripture fore‑telleth , that many ſhall be deceived , and drawn away by men ſpeaking perverſe things , and made merchandize of by falſe teachers , even thoſe that have obtained like precious faith, and therefore ſaith he unto them, beware lea alſo ye being led away by the error of the wicked, fall from your own edfanee , again, beware lea any man ſpoil you through Philoſophy and vain deceit, after the Traditions of men , after the rudiments of the world, and not after Chri, let no man beguile you &c. and again, behold I come quickly, hold fa that which thou ha let no man take thy crown : all which teacheth us,that be‑ lievers may fall away if they do not take heed , beware and and fa &c. and that the Scripture did fore‑ſee that ſome ſhould fall , be ſpoiled , and deceived, through their not taking heed , therefore believers in Chri may fall away.
